WEBVTT

00:10:56.833 --> 00:11:00.643
This idea consumed me for months.

00:11:00.667 --> 00:11:05.518
It was the most intense
intellectual experience of my life.

00:11:05.542 --> 00:11:08.143
On every bike ride to lab,

00:11:08.167 --> 00:11:10.684
on every walk to the coffee shop,

00:11:10.708 --> 00:11:13.601
on every run in the hills above campus,

00:11:13.625 --> 00:11:15.601
the ideas, the arguments,

00:11:15.625 --> 00:11:16.934
the counterarguments,

00:11:16.958 --> 00:11:20.184
they all came so rapidly in my head,
in my inner monologue,

00:11:20.208 --> 00:11:21.958
that I was physically out of breath.

00:11:22.667 --> 00:11:26.476
I thought if we can create
a therapy that replicates,

00:11:26.500 --> 00:11:28.292
it would only need to be taken once.

00:11:29.500 --> 00:11:32.226
It could mutate along with the virus